13. Cormorant:  Unmanned  aircraft  that  can  be  launched  from  a  submarine  and

retrieved at the end of a mission.

14. Data  in  Optical  Domain—Network:  All-optical  communications  with  optical

coding, storage, multiplexing, and routing.

15. Defense  Against  Cyber  Attacks  on  Mobile  Ad  Hoc  Network  Systems:
Cognitive,  autonomous,  information  assurance  tools  for  next-generation,  yet-to-
be-deployed, tactical military networks.

16. Disruption  Tolerant  Networking:  Replacing  the  connection  oriented  philos-
ophy  of  today’s  Internet  with  protocols  that  guarantee  message  delivery,  even
when connections are disrupted.

17. Dynamic  Quarantine  of  Computer-Based  Worms:  Computer  defenses  that

operate ‘‘faster-than-worm-speed’’ against zero-day worms.

18. Electronic  and  Photonic  Integrated  Circuits:  Ubiquitous  photonics  pro-

duced on the same wafer as silicon microelectronics.

19. Engineered  Bio-Molecular  Nano-Devices/Systems:  Engineered  bio-molec-
ular  nanoscale  devices  that  emulate  the  behavior  of  membrane  ion  channels  to
enable real-time observation and analysis of bio-molecular signals, enabling sin-
gle-molecule sensitivity.

