ruses  and  worms.  And  if  they  have,  I  would  be  very  interested  to
see that technology. And I think our government would be very in-
terested in having it deployed to protect ourselves. We are basically
defenseless today against viruses and worms.

Dr. TETHER. I agree, and I would be very happy to actually show
them what we are doing, but it does require classified information.
The slammer worm that was a—what we did with the mutation,
just  to  get  technical,  was  that  we  made  it  into  a  single  packet
worm so a signature detection couldn’t detect the worm. And it was
not just replicating.

We  also  did  the  hard  test.  We  had  an  insider.  In  other  words,
this worm was released into the network pretending that there was
somebody  inside  the  network  who  let  it  go.  So  it  wasn’t  coming
through  the  perimeter.  It  was  inside.  And  yeah,  he  is  right  that

