87

flect  on  their  own  behavior.  In  other  words,  you  are  talking  about
a computer considerably smarter than my last opponent.

We are in the spin business. I know that the Administration and
the  science  establishment  doesn’t  want  to  fund  research  into
whether we should create what I would refer to loosely as a silicon-
based  intelligent  lifeform  and  does  not  even  want  to  research  the
much  more  technical  issue  of  how  we  develop  higher  and  higher
levels  of  computer  capacity  while  deliberately  engineering  devices
to  make  sure  that  we  do  not  create  self-awareness.  I  would  point
out  that  many  of  those  who  have  thought  about  the  issue  of  when
will  we  know  that  computers  deserve  the  minimum  wage  have  de-
