to get to.

So,  for  example,  in  all  of  the  work  on  cryptographic  algorithms,
the method of cryptography is published broadly. It is only the key
that  you  have  to  depend  on.  So  if  it  is  necessary  to  classify  some
of  this  material,  I  can  see  classification,  by  the  way,  for  offensive
techniques.  But  if  it  is  necessary  to  classify  defensive  techniques,
they are probably not very strong techniques.

Chairman  BOEHLERT.  Look,  let  me  just  ask  you  something  else,
